HEADWORD: Lyra
<hw>Ly"ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>lyra</ets>,
Gr. <?/. See <er>Lyre</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld>
<def>A northern constellation, the Harp, containing a white star of the
first magnitude, called <member>Alpha Lyr⟦ae⟧</member>, or
<member>Vega</member>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The middle portion of the ventral
surface of the fornix of the brain; -- so called from the arrangement of
the lines with which it is marked in the human brain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lyraid</ent>⟦br⟧
